txt.en: Seat of the Great Goblin
'Ho, ho! So, finally you arrive...'
'Are you all content to sit by and see me slain?!'
'Not so soon, you monsters! My reign had just begun...'
'Aid me, you wretches!'
'Intruders... Send word to Uloga!'
'Ah, the crown... my chance arrives at last!'
'Uloga was weak! I shall show you how Great a goblin can be!'
'And who is this miserable lot?'
'Curse you, you pathetic lot!'
'Thieves come to pick away at the treasures of my people?'
'Murderers, sent by those wretched Elves?'
'No matter... who are you to storm so brazenly through my domain?'
'I have dealt with your folk before, and so I shall again!'
'Come, my subject, this Great one demands your service...'
'Down! Down!'
'You lot, to my side or I'll kill you myself!'
'More of you! More! Slay these wretches!
'How can so many of you accomplish so little?!'
'Beat and batter!'
'Aid me or I'll feed you to the Wargs!'
'You miserable brutes... so be it!'
'You think yourselves bold? Clever?'
'Weaklings all dead! Got what they deserved! Goblin-town is MINE!'
'Tasty flesh, my pets... Kill, kill! The scraps are yours!'
'But I am the Great... Goblin...'
'Neither your precious wizard or his weapons of ages past will save you from my people this time!'
'Die! Die! Die!'
'Bite! Chew! Rip them apart!'
